1
00:00:03,291 --> 00:00:05,500
[ Audience murmuring ]

2
00:00:06,291 --> 00:00:07,958
Huh?

3
00:00:10,041 --> 00:00:19,875
[ Murmuring fades ]

4
00:00:19,958 --> 00:00:21,333
[ Note chimes ]

5
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:23,666
[ Gasping ]

6
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:28,416
<i>In that moment,</i>
<i>my fate was set.</i>

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,666
[ playing
"Etude, Opus 25, Number 11" ]

8
00:00:45,791 --> 00:00:49,208
MOTHER: Why'd you wanna come to
the park all of a sudden, Emi?

9
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:52,000
FATHER: Be careful.
You're really high up.

10
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:58,291
I'm Emi,
and I'm gonna play piano!

11
00:00:58,375 --> 00:01:00,375
EMI:
<i>On top of the jungle gym,</i>

12
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:03,375
<i>I pledged myself</i>
<i>to the life of a pianist.</i>

13
00:01:03,458 --> 00:01:05,250
[ Piano music continues ]

14
00:01:11,291 --> 00:01:16,000
<i>I set aside all other ambitions</i>
<i>for the sake of one.</i>

15
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,458
<i>Return to me.</i>

16
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:20,000
<i>Return to me.</i>

17
00:01:20,875 --> 00:01:21,958
OCHIAI:
Why, hello.

18
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:24,291
MOTHER:
She won't bite, honey.

19
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:28,916
A pleasure to meet you.
I'm Yuriko Ochiai.

20
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,041
Can you tell me your name?

21
00:01:33,916 --> 00:01:35,166
I wanna...

22
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:36,500
Go on.

23
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:37,791
I wanna play

24
00:01:37,875 --> 00:01:40,500
and make people who hear me
wanna play!

25
00:01:40,583 --> 00:01:41,916
[ Whimpers ]

26
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,875
Can -- Can you make me good
at the piano like that?

27
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:47,500
I want it more than anything
in the world!

28
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,416
<i>Return to me.</i>

29
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:52,375
OCHIAI:
If you work hard enough, Emi,

30
00:01:52,458 --> 00:01:54,708
I'm sure your music
will touch people, too.

31
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:57,291
The piano has a way
of listening.

32
00:01:57,375 --> 00:01:59,333
Can I play it?

33
00:01:59,416 --> 00:02:02,833
Of course you can.

34
00:02:02,916 --> 00:02:04,958
[ Gasps ]

35
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:11,708
[ Grunts ]

36
00:02:13,208 --> 00:02:15,000
[ Note plays ]
[ Screams ]

37
00:02:16,791 --> 00:02:20,000
That's the only kind of sound
I can make with it?

38
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:21,333
<i>But when that boy was playing,</i>

39
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:25,333
<i>everything sounded</i>
<i>like sunflowers.</i>

40
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:30,125
<i>I just wanted to play</i>
<i>like you, Arima.</i>

41
00:02:30,875 --> 00:02:33,708
Every great performer
started out right where you are,

42
00:02:33,791 --> 00:02:35,375
having never played before.

43
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:38,666
Even the likes of Mozart
and Beethoven were new once.

44
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:40,291
Whoever inspired you,

45
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:42,666
they went through
this same thing.

46
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:46,583
Now, my dear,
pretend the piano is a genie.

47
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:49,375
What would you wish for?

48
00:02:52,583 --> 00:02:54,000
<i>I want...</i>

49
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:57,750
YOUNG EMI:
<i>I wanna...</i>

50
00:02:57,833 --> 00:03:01,333
<i>I wanna play the piano</i>
<i>like that boy did.</i>

51
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:04,708
<i>I want to stand</i>
<i>on the same stage as him.</i>

52
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:10,500
<i>Once I can play</i>
<i>as good as him...</i>

53
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:17,833
<i>...I'll see all those</i>
<i>sunflowers he shared with us.</i>

54
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,916
[ "Etude, Opus 25, Number 11"
continues ]

55
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:40,291
<i>Let it ring.</i>

56
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:41,625
BOTH:
<i>Let it ring.</i>

57
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:43,958
EMI:
<i>Let it ring.</i>

58
00:04:08,875 --> 00:04:10,750
[ Exhales deeply ]

59
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:13,000
[ Audience cheering ]

60
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:22,791
<i>Let it ring.</i>

61
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:30,083
[ "Hikaru Nara" playing ]

62
00:04:42,416 --> 00:04:44,583
[ Singing in Japanese ]

63
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:58,916
[ Applause ]

64
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,791
TAKESHI:
Is that girl for real or what?

65
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:03,000
That was crazy just now.

66
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:05,791
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

67
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:10,750
Well played.
That was great.

68
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,625
[ Breathing heavily ]
Huh?

69
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,041
[ Grunts ]

70
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:20,375
[ Breathing heavily ]

71
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:28,750
Listen, Arima!

72
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:31,291
[ Breathing heavily ]

73
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:38,083
<i>Wait!</i>
<i>Is she confessing her love?</i>

74
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:48,833
Sorry.
I'm gonna go change.

75
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:50,041
Yeah.

76
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:52,875
'Cause it is kind of chilly
back here.

77
00:06:52,958 --> 00:06:54,875
[ Grunts ]
<i>Come on!</i>

78
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:58,916
EMI:<i> Right now,</i>
<i>there's no need for words.</i>

79
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,500
<i>I said it all with my piano.</i>

80
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:04,666
WOMAN:<i> There will now be</i>
<i>an intermission.</i>

81
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:07,666
<i>Judging will resume</i>
<i>in 15 minutes.</i>

82
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:09,875
[ Water running ]

83
00:07:19,416 --> 00:07:21,625
You think there's something
wrong with that girl?

84
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:23,833
That was a bunch of pills
she just took.

85
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:24,916
Yeah.

86
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,500
[ Indistinct conversations ]
Huh?

87
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:30,583
Hey, that girl's pretty hot.
You feeling okay, Tsubaki?

88
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:32,625
The closer we get
to Kousei's turn,

89
00:07:32,708 --> 00:07:34,833
the more my stomach hurts.

90
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:37,958
I don't even get this nervous
before a softball game.

91
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,666
You've got the easy job
today.

92
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,541
You get to sit back and watch.
Just try to relax.

93
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,916
But I'm worried about Kousei.
I see a hot mom over there.

94
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,500
Bet you he's
freaking out right now.

95
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,500
That girl's performance
was amazing.

96
00:07:48,583 --> 00:07:50,916
How's he supposed to come out
and play after that?

97
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,833
Give the guy
a little credit, yeah?

98
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:55,791
Kousei's gonna man up.
I know it.

99
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:57,791
[ Fingers tapping ]
WOMAN:<i> Attention.</i>

100
00:07:57,875 --> 00:07:59,833
<i>The competition</i>
<i>will now resume.</i>

101
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:02,500
[ Heartbeat echoing ]

102
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,333
<i>Oh, man. My heart.</i>

103
00:08:06,416 --> 00:08:08,875
<i>It's pounding even harder</i>
<i>than it was before.</i>

104
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:11,208
[ Heart beating ]

105
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,916
[ Gasps ]

106
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,791
♪♪

107
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:29,750
TAKESHI:
<i>Arima's gonna play Chopin's</i>

108
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:32,750
<i>"Etude Opus 25,</i>
<i>Number 5" today,</i>

109
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,166
<i>but that song is way too easy.</i>

110
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,000
<i>What the hell?!</i>

111
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,333
<i>Back when he was competing,</i>
<i>Arima banked on his ability</i>

112
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:43,750
<i>to play difficult songs</i>
<i>to perfection.</i>

113
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,750
<i>Knowing that about him</i>
<i>was the whole reason</i>

114
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:49,000
<i>I chose "Winter Wind"</i>
<i>to be my piece today.</i>

115
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:51,083
<i>Takeshi knows it, too.</i>

116
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:54,166
<i>But the song that Arima</i>
<i>picked for this,</i>

117
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,250
<i>it's not difficult at all.</i>

118
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,375
<i>What's his angle, huh?</i>

119
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:01,750
How'd you pick out
Kousei's song for today anyhow?

120
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:02,875
[ Chuckles ]

121
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:07,041
The pencil landed on 25-5!

122
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:09,041
You sealed my fate
with a pencil?!

123
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:10,625
Pencil!
Got it!

124
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:11,666
[ Laughs ]

125
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,708
He could play "Chopsticks"
for all that I care.

126
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:18,458
What matters is that he's here.

127
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:22,166
[ Music continues ]

128
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:25,166
Kousei's here,
and he's gonna play.

129
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:28,625
Kousei Arima?
You're the next one up.

130
00:09:28,708 --> 00:09:30,041
Thank you.

131
00:09:30,541 --> 00:09:33,041
Just being
in this recital hall,

132
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:35,875
it's waking up
a part of his soul.

133
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:38,041
I know he'll rise
to the occasion.

134
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:40,666
His rivals are out for blood,

135
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:42,958
and he can't ignore
that challenge.

136
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,750
He'll give it everything
he's got.

137
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:48,291
He will,
because Kousei's a musician.

138
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:54,208
<i>Two years.</i>
<i>Has it really been that long?</i>

139
00:09:54,291 --> 00:09:57,000
<i>My heart is pounding so hard,</i>

140
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:59,583
<i>like an animal</i>
<i>thrashing around.</i>

141
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:03,208
<i>Is it because I watched</i>
<i>those two play just now?</i>

142
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:05,791
<i>No holding back.</i>
<i>No safety net.</i>

143
00:10:05,875 --> 00:10:09,833
<i>They poured their souls</i>
<i>into those pieces.</i>

144
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:11,916
<i>This is who I am!</i>

145
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,958
<i>Let it ring!</i>

146
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:18,333
<i>I'm the same as you.</i>

147
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,958
Whatever stopped in him
that day,

148
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:23,125
it's about to start again.

149
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:25,375
<i>Kaori?</i>

150
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,791
[ Applause ]

151
00:10:27,875 --> 00:10:33,208
<i>I never noticed music</i>
<i>can have a color so vibrant,</i>

152
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:34,583
<i>even a smell.</i>

153
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:36,583
Are you ready?

154
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:39,458
I know he's going to walk out
on that stage.

155
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:44,250
<i>My blood is boiling,</i>
<i>and it's all because of music!</i>

156
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,250
<i>Go time.</i>

157
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:48,041
WOMAN:
Hey, that's Arima.

158
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:49,166
MAN:
Really?

159
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:51,166
[ Footsteps echoing ]

160
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:54,000
<i>Here we go.</i>

161
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:55,791
<i>I thought</i>
<i>I was nervous before,</i>

162
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:58,875
<i>but now --</i>
<i>Just hang in there, belly!</i>

163
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:00,208
Huh?

164
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:02,875
[ Sighs ]
I'm guessing it's his turn.

165
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:08,416
[ Gasps ]

166
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:15,583
CAT:<i> Are you ready</i>
<i>to go on your journey?</i>

167
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:18,750
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

168
00:11:21,666 --> 00:11:23,083
Wanna play dodgeball
with us?

169
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:25,916
I promise not to hit you
too hard.

170
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,416
Sorry, but...

171
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:30,208
I'm in the middle
of a piano lesson with Mom.

172
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:33,000
Again?
For reals?

173
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:35,750
Huh? What happened to your arm?
It's all bruised.

174
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:38,583
Oh, I knocked it into something,
but I'm okay.

175
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,958
You're, like, the clumsiest kid
I know.

176
00:11:41,041 --> 00:11:41,958
SAKI: Kousei!
[ Gasps ]

177
00:11:42,041 --> 00:11:43,833
You get back here right now!

178
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:46,000
That was super scary.

179
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:49,083
Mom's calling for me, Tsubaki.
I gotta go.

180
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,291
Maybe next time?

181
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:52,958
Okay.
Good luck with the piano.

182
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:54,625
Mm.

183
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:57,541
[ Music continues ]

184
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:06,458
Time to sit down, Kousei.

185
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:13,625
<i>Come.</i>
<i>What are you waiting for?</i>

186
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:14,958
<i>Let's begin.</i>

187
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:17,083
[ Gasps ]

188
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:23,166
KOUSEI:
[ Breathing heavily ]

189
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,916
WOMAN: No running in the halls,
please.

190
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,625
Sorry!

191
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:29,458
Hey, Mom! I brought you
some clean clothes from home.

192
00:12:29,541 --> 00:12:31,416
Hey, Kousei.

193
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,666
Sorry I couldn't be there.
This was the big day, right?

194
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,833
Uh-huh.
I won first place.

195
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:38,541
Check out my certificate.

196
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:41,583
But Haydn's so tough for you.

197
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:43,875
That's why I practiced
a bunch.

198
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,583
That's a good boy.

199
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:49,125
I take a lot of pills,

200
00:12:49,208 --> 00:12:52,000
but you spreading your wings
like this,

201
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:54,458
that's the best medicine
for me.

202
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:58,166
[ Sighs ] Then I'm --
I'm gonna keep coming in first

203
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:01,125
so you can keep feeling better
and better.

204
00:13:02,208 --> 00:13:05,125
I'll get first
as many times as it takes.

205
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,416
<i>I promise.</i>

206
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,916
[ Heartbeat echoing ]

207
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,166
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

208
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:16,458
MAN: What's he doing?

209
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:18,458
WOMAN:
He's just standing there.

210
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:21,916
[ Audience murmuring ]

211
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:26,375
<i>Don't be afraid.</i>
<i>You're fine.</i>

212
00:13:36,791 --> 00:13:38,416
[ Music continues ]

213
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:41,541
<i>Damn it.</i>
<i>It's overpowering me.</i>

214
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:47,250
<i>It scares all of us.</i>

215
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,666
[ Chord echoing ]

216
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,083
<i>Now play.</i>

217
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,666
<i>Now play.</i>

218
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,125
<i>Now play.</i>

219
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,583
<i>Now play!</i>

220
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:59,583
[ Playing "Etude Opus 25,
Number 5" ]

221
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:06,708
[ Exhales deeply ]
<i>He's in the spotlight,</i>

222
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:09,250
<i>like he never left</i>
<i>in the first place.</i>

223
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:10,750
<i>He's returned,</i>

224
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,833
<i>the invincible pianist</i>
<i>in a league all his own,</i>

225
00:14:13,916 --> 00:14:17,500
<i>the one I looked up to --</i>
<i>Kousei Arima.</i>

226
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:20,000
<i>Impeccable form.</i>

227
00:14:20,083 --> 00:14:21,500
<i>He's perfect,</i>

228
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:23,791
<i>playing it exactly</i>
<i>as it's shown in the score.</i>

229
00:14:23,875 --> 00:14:27,583
<i>And the music that results</i>
<i>might as well be a glacier.</i>

230
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:30,166
<i>Two years later,</i>
<i>nothing has changed.</i>

231
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,500
<i>I can hear the notes,</i>
<i>loud and clear.</i>

232
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:37,125
<i>I can play the score</i>
<i>exactly as I've memorized it.</i>

233
00:14:37,208 --> 00:14:40,916
<i>Muscle memory will guide me</i>
<i>through this,</i>

234
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,375
<i>like riding a bike.</i>

235
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:45,333
It's your entry.
How do you want to play it?

236
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:47,958
<i>I'm playing</i>
<i>the way I always did.</i>

237
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:49,583
SAKI:
<i>That's how it should be.</i>

238
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:52,125
<i>Your job is to honor</i>
<i>the composer's vision,</i>

239
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:53,833
<i>not go on flights of fancy!</i>

240
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:57,250
<i>You know</i>
<i>that's the path to victory.</i>

241
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,625
<i>Now, then, are you</i>
<i>going to bring home</i>

242
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:04,166
<i>another first place</i>
<i>for your mother or aren't you?</i>

243
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,666
[ Footsteps approaching ]

244
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:08,125
TSUBAKI: You were playing
the piano all day again, huh?

245
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:10,291
Yeah, but I had
to run to the store.

246
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:11,791
Dad's still away
on business,

247
00:15:11,875 --> 00:15:14,458
so I had to make sure
me and Mom were good for food.

248
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:15,916
[ Laughs ]
What the...

249
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,625
All you bought
are egg sandwiches.

250
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:19,375
Get a little creative,
why don't you?

251
00:15:19,458 --> 00:15:21,083
She won't let me use
the stove,

252
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:22,875
so there weren't
a lot of choices.

253
00:15:22,958 --> 00:15:25,083
We've got some leftovers
from last night.

254
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:26,958
I'll bring 'em over for you,
okay?

255
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,625
Hey, Kousei, how's your mom
been feeling lately?

256
00:15:29,708 --> 00:15:32,375
I heard my folks talking about
how she was still all sick

257
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:33,500
or something.

258
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:34,916
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

259
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,208
She told me she'd be going
into the hospital soon.

260
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:41,000
Really?
But how come?

261
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:45,500
All I know
is it's my fault.

262
00:15:45,583 --> 00:15:48,291
Huh?
What'd you say?

263
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:50,833
Just forget it.

264
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:54,166
<i>Mom wouldn't be so sick</i>
<i>if it weren't for me.</i>

265
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:58,000
<i>If I played how she told me,</i>
<i>this wouldn't have happened.</i>

266
00:15:58,083 --> 00:16:01,416
<i>And so I'm gonna win</i>
<i>first place,</i>

267
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:04,333
<i>'cause she's sure</i>
<i>to get better then.</i>

268
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,291
<i>Arima won again?</i>

269
00:16:06,375 --> 00:16:08,958
[ Groans ]<i> Leave it</i>
<i>to the Human Metronome.</i>

270
00:16:09,041 --> 00:16:10,208
[ Laughs ]

271
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:11,875
<i>Just go to Europe already.</i>

272
00:16:11,958 --> 00:16:14,708
<i>Bland and lifeless.</i>
<i>He's holding us back.</i>

273
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,208
<i>He's nothing but</i>
<i>his mother's puppet, anyway.</i>

274
00:16:17,291 --> 00:16:20,041
KOUSEI:
<i>Shut up, all of you.</i>

275
00:16:20,125 --> 00:16:22,333
<i>None of them know</i>
<i>what they're talking about.</i>

276
00:16:22,416 --> 00:16:25,416
<i>It's me and my mom</i>
<i>versus everybody else.</i>

277
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:29,416
Next time I perform,
my mom is gonna come

278
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:32,041
all the way from the hospital
to cheer me on.

279
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,208
Oh!
Really?

280
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,666
That must mean she's feeling
a lot better, then.

281
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,000
I'm so glad!

282
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:41,000
I guess that visit from me
raised her spirits, huh?

283
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,416
I did bring a gift.

284
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:45,333
Scented erasers
were kind of a random choice.

285
00:16:46,166 --> 00:16:49,333
<i>Up near the exit on</i>
<i>the left side of the audience,</i>

286
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:51,333
<i>somewhere I can see her.</i>

287
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:54,625
<i>Today that's my mom's</i>
<i>special seat.</i>

288
00:16:55,958 --> 00:16:58,541
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>she's really here.</i>

289
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,583
Yeah.
Thank you.

290
00:17:00,666 --> 00:17:02,083
And guess what, you guys.

291
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:04,916
I'm gonna play so well
while my mom is watching

292
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,791
that she'll feel
all the way better.

293
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:10,125
That way, she can finally
come home for good.

294
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:15,416
[ Audience cheering ]

295
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,750
[ Grunts ]
Saki, he's just a kid!

296
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,250
Your performance was garbage!

297
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:24,250
How many times have I told you
to review the goddamn score?!

298
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:26,041
How many times?!
You can't
just keep hitting him!

299
00:17:26,125 --> 00:17:27,458
Oh, God.

300
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:29,500
But he played better today
than I'd ever seen before.

301
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:31,083
I'm going to go get
a staff member.

302
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:34,666
You played what you felt instead
of what was written down!

303
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:36,625
[ Gasps ]

304
00:17:36,708 --> 00:17:39,083
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

305
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:46,958
<i>You're not going to bed</i>
<i>until you play it right.</i>

306
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,250
<i>What are you, a damn beginner?</i>

307
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:50,958
<i>You're worthless!</i>

308
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:53,541
I'm in the middle
of a piano lesson with Mom.

309
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:55,208
For reals?

310
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:57,416
<i>You always ruin that part!</i>

311
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,458
<i>That kid's got bruises</i>
<i>all over him.</i>

312
00:17:59,541 --> 00:18:02,041
<i>I bet you that's why he</i>
<i>always wears long sleeves.</i>

313
00:18:02,125 --> 00:18:06,208
<i>So she hits her own son?</i>
<i>She's a monster.</i>

314
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:11,000
[ Gasps ]

315
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:14,375
How dare you throw that score!
Pick it up now!

316
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:18,708
KOUSEI: All I wanted
was for you to be happy.

317
00:18:18,791 --> 00:18:20,958
[ Gasps ]

318
00:18:21,916 --> 00:18:24,541
Even when I just wanted
to play with my friends

319
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:28,000
or you hit me,
I sat back down at the piano

320
00:18:28,083 --> 00:18:30,416
and kept practicing,
'cause I thought

321
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:34,166
if I did a good enough job
as a pianist, you'd get better.

322
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:37,166
[ Sobs ]
That's why I took all the pain.

323
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,500
To save you!

324
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,958
That's over now.

325
00:18:43,375 --> 00:18:45,625
'Cause I don't care anymore.

326
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:48,583
Now I just wish you were dead.

327
00:18:56,416 --> 00:18:58,500
[ Playing "Moonlight Sonata" ]

328
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:03,375
<i>Those words were the last thing</i>
<i>I said to her...</i>

329
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:04,375
<i>ever.</i>

330
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:06,791
[ Music continues ]

331
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:10,500
Hey, Kousei.

332
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:11,416
Yeah?

333
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,458
You gonna do the finals?

334
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:17,708
Uh-huh.
I made it through prelims, so...

335
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,583
[ Sighs ]

336
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:23,208
I know it's awful.

337
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,500
My mother just passed away,
and here I am

338
00:19:25,583 --> 00:19:29,416
worrying about some competition
that's a few days later.

339
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,833
What kind of person
does that?

340
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:34,458
Are you okay?

341
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:37,000
Yeah.
I'll be fine.

342
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:39,875
After all, I'm doing
what Mom trained me to.

343
00:19:41,083 --> 00:19:44,291
<i>When I think back to that day,</i>
<i>I can't see her face.</i>

344
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:45,583
[ Music continues ]

345
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:46,875
<i>Nothing.</i>

346
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:49,291
<i>A black hole</i>
<i>staring back at me.</i>

347
00:19:49,375 --> 00:19:51,125
[ Music continues ]

348
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:53,958
His mother just died,
didn't she?

349
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:56,458
How can he play
like everything's fine?

350
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:58,958
The apple doesn't fall
far from the tree.

351
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:01,458
He's not even off
by a fraction.

352
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:03,750
Like mother, like son.

353
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,125
[ Music continues ]

354
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:06,666
KOUSEI:
<i>Up near the exit</i>

355
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:09,666
<i>on the left side</i>
<i>of the audience,</i>

356
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,541
<i>a spot where I could see her.</i>

357
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:14,958
<i>That was my mom's special seat.</i>

358
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:19,083
<i>And this...</i>
<i>this is my punishment.</i>

359
00:20:19,166 --> 00:20:20,791
[ Gasps ]

360
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:23,666
[ Heartbeat echoing ]

361
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:26,791
[ playing
"Etude, Opus 25, Number 11" ]

362
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:29,708
[ Heartbeat slows, fades ]

363
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:33,291
[ Music continues ]

364
00:20:33,375 --> 00:20:36,375
SAKI:<i> You're right.</i>
<i>This</i> is<i> punishment.</i>

365
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:38,625
<i>You deserve this.</i>

366
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:41,791
<i>You understand that,</i>
<i>don't you, my darling Kousei?</i>

367
00:20:41,875 --> 00:20:43,791
[ Wind blowing ]

368
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,041
[ Gasps ]

369
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:47,833
[ Off-key music playing,
keys thudding ]

370
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,000
<i>The notes...</i>

371
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:55,333
[ Gasps ]
What the...

372
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:59,875
<i>The sound of the piano --</i>
<i>I've lost it.</i>

373
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,083
<i>He's unraveling.</i>

374
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,333
That poor boy.

375
00:21:04,416 --> 00:21:06,583
Can't even hear the notes
anymore, they say.

376
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:08,916
[ Music continues ]

377
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:15,125
[ Distorted music playing ]

378
00:21:15,208 --> 00:21:17,291
[ Water bubbling ]

379
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:24,500
[ "Kirameki" playing ]

380
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,916
[ Singing in Japanese ]

